tent":"Explicit tick values or count with `xTickValues` / `yTickValues` or `xNumTicks` / `yNumTicks`."},"1295":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-60","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#band-padding","content":"Outer padding on a band-scale axis with `xPaddingOuter` / `yPaddingOuter`."},"1296":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-61","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#tooltip-disabled","content":"Tooltip, crosshair, and data point glyphs all disabled (`tooltip={false}`, `showCrosshair={false}`, `showDataPoints={false}`)."},"1297":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-62","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#crosshair-only","content":"Only the vertical crosshair on hover; tooltip and data point glyphs disabled."},"1298":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-63","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#custom-tooltip-formatting","content":"Tooltip values formatted with `tooltipValueFormatter` (e.g. currency, units)."},"1299":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-64","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#custom-accessors","content":"Custom data shape (e.g. `date`/`value`) with `xAccessor` and `yAccessor`."},"1300":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-65","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#missing-values","content":"Null Y values create breaks in the line."},"1301":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-66","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#fixed-size","content":"Explicit chart size via `width` and `height` props (e.g. 800×400)."},"1302":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-67","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#bitcoin-price","content":"Time-series with date and currency formatting, gridlines, and nice Y-axis."},"1303":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-68","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#city-temperature","content":"Multiple series over time with legend, shared time axis, and temperature (°F) formatting."},"1304":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-69","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#browser-usage","content":"Categorical X-axis (band scale) with multiple series and percentage formatting."},"1305":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-70","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#right-to-left","content":"The chart follows the current **layout direction** (LTR or RTL). By default, that direction is detected automatically from the browser or system settings. When it is RTL, the chart mirrors axes and labels accordingly."},"1306":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-71","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#data-attributes","content":"The chart root exposes data attributes that reflect prop state for styling:"},"1307":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-72","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#data-attributes","content":"**Chart container:** `data-width`, `data-height`, `data-x-labels`, `data-y-labels`, `data-x-labels-vertical`, `data-x-baseline`, `data-y-baseline`, `data-x-tick-marks`, `data-y-tick-marks`"},"1308":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-73","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#component-customization","content":"Use the `className` prop on the chart container to add or override styles:"},"1309":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-74","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"Provide &#x2A;*`aria-label`** to describe the chart (e.g. \"Monthly sales revenue from January to May 2024\")."},"1310":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-75","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"Use &#x2A;*`desc`** for a longer description rendered in the SVG `<desc>` for screen readers."},"1311":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-76","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"The component sets ARIA attributes on interactive and structural elements as needed."},"1312":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-77","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#chart-not-sizing-or-empty","content":"Ensure the chart has a non-zero size. Place it in a container with explicit dimensions or use `width` and `height`:"},"1313":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-78","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#dates-not-displaying-correctly","content":"Use `xType=\"time\"` when the X-axis values are Date objects:"},"1314":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-79","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#tooltip-or-crosshair-not-showing","content":"Ensure `tooltip`, `showCrosshair`, or `showDataPoints` are not set to `false`, and that the chart receives pointer events (e.g. no overlay blocking hover)."},"1315":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-80","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Use for trends over time or along a continuous scale."},"1316":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-81","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Use when comparing a few series (e.g. 2–5 lines); avoid too many overlapping lines."},"1317":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-82","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Prefer a single chart with a legend over multiple small charts when comparing the same X range."},"1318":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"page","content":"DonutChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart"},"1319":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","content":"Donut charts are for parts-to-whole comparison—how partial elements add up to a total—shown as a ring so a few categories are easy to compare at a glance."},"1320":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#installation","content":"Installation"},"1321":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#props","content":"Props"},"1322":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#examples","content":"Examples"},"1323":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#basic","content":"Basic"},"1324":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#single-slice","content":"Single slice"},"1325":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#legend-placement","content":"Legend placement"},"1326":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#small-slices","content":"Small slices"},"1327":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-8","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#format-value","content":"Format value"},"1328":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-9","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#basic","content":"You give the chart a `data` array (`id`, `name`, `value`) and a `label` in the middle—this is the everyday setup when you want several categories on one ring and a headline number or title in the hole."},"1329":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-10","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#single-slice","content":"When there is only one slice, the ring is full. Add `subLabel` if you want a smaller second line under the main center text."},"1330":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-11","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#legend-placement","content":"Switch `legend` to `right` to sit the legend beside the donut, or `bottom` to stack it underneath. `legendLabel` is there when you want a title above the legend items."},"1331":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#small-slices","content":"Very thin slices can be noisy to hover. Anything at or below `smallSliceThreshold` (default `0.05` of the total) is treated as “small,” and if those slices sit next to each other on the ring, one hover opens a single tooltip that lists the whole group."},"1332":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#format-value","content":"Use `formatValue` when the raw numbers in the tooltip should read like money, counts with separators, or whatever your product expects. The percentage of the total still formats on its own; your function only shapes the value column."},"1333":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart","type":"page","content":"Gauge Chart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart"},"1334":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart","content":"A visual indicator for representing a single quantitative value within a known range, rendered as a semicircle arc in continuous or segmented mode."},"1335":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart#installation","content":"Installation"},"1336":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart#props","content":"Props"},"1337":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-c